      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/activity-score-robustness-assessment/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "if all of the samples in a single experimental factor have intensities of zero, these are replaced by a minimum intensity value (which can be set by the user), and if only some of the sample values in a factor are zero, then these are replaced by the mean value of the nonzero samples in that factor... Intermediate users can run PALS as a standalone command-line tool and incorporate PALS into a workflow as part of a custom script.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms configurable min_replace parameter and command-line tool, but does not explicitly name a 'noise parameter' for noise injection. The robustness testing uses synthetic decoy features and missing data removal, not a named 'noise parameter'.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo11020103",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "activity-score-robustness-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools[role]",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "PALS enables robustness testing via programmatic API and command-line batch processing with configurable min_replace and noise parameters",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:36:20.386000+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/activity-score-robustness-assessment/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "the intensity matrix is subsequently transformed to log space and standardised using the preprocessing module in Scipy [27] such that each factor has a zero mean and unit variance across the samples... PALS was used to assess the activity levels of potentially unknown metabolites grouped into molecular families (MFs) through their fragmentation spectral similarities, and into Mass2Motifs based on shared fragment and neutral loss features.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms log-transformation and standardization of intensity matrices, and analysis of Molecular Families and Mass2Motifs.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo11020103",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "activity-score-robustness-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "After computing PLAGE-derived activity scores for pathways or metabolite sets (Molecular Families, Mass2Motifs) from log2-standardized metabolomics intensity data.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:36:20.386000+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/activity-score-robustness-assessment/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "A comparison of mPLAGE with two other commonly used methods (overrepresentation analysis (ORA) and gene set enrichment analysis (GSEA)) is also given and reveals that mPLAGE is more robust to missing features and noisy data than the alternatives.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly compares mPLAGE to ORA and GSEA for robustness to missing and noisy data.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo11020103",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "activity-score-robustness-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Compare PLAGE results to alternative methods (ORA, GSEA) to confirm the method's advantage in handling incomplete peak data.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:36:20.386000+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/comparative-enrichment-method-evaluation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The robustness of mPLAGE was evaluated on both synthetic and real data experiments and compared to both ORA and GSEA methods... To assess the robustness of mPLAGE, benchmarking experiments were performed... To mimic the inclusion of formulae that arise due to incorrect identification/annotation, decoy features were generated... To simulate missing features, which often occurs in real metabolomics data, features were also randomly removed from pathways with a uniform probability of 0.2.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper does benchmark PALS/ORA/GSEA with controlled noise (decoy features) and missing data. However, robustness is measured using precision, recall, F1 score, and p-value distributions\u2014NOT rank correlation or effect size preservation as claimed. The card overstates the specific metrics used.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo11020103",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "comparative-enrichment-method-evaluation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Systematically benchmark pathway/metabolite set enrichment methods (PALS, ORA, GSEA) by introducing controlled levels of noise and missing peaks into metabolomics peak data, then measuring robustness using rank correlation and effect size preservation.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:36:40.502260+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/comparative-enrichment-method-evaluation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To summarise overall performance, the F1 score, which is a harmonic mean of precision and recall and defined as F1=(2\u2217Prec\u2217Rec)/(Prec+Rec), is used... Assessing changes to the p-values of the true changing pathways with higher number of decoy features reveals that increasing the number of decoy features generally produces higher p-values",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses F1 score, precision, recall, and p-value analysis. No mention of rank correlation or effect size preservation metrics.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo11020103",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "comparative-enrichment-method-evaluation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "measuring robustness using rank correlation and effect size preservation",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:36:40.502260+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/comparative-enrichment-method-evaluation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here, we present PALS (Pathway Activity Level Scoring), a Python library, command line tool, and Web application that performs the ranking of significantly changing metabolite sets over different experimental conditions.",
      "asbval:note": null,
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo11020103",
