      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "PALS can be run either as a standalone tool, imported as a Python library, or used via a Web interface allowing users with a wide range of expertise and requirements to use it... To assist beginners, a Web interface is provided to run PALS in an intuitive and user-friendly manner.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms a Web interface exists for PALS, but does not explicitly name it 'PALS Viewer' or detail file upload/visualization capabilities. The paper mentions 'PALS Viewer' only in passing in passage [10] as an 'interactive Web application' but provides no functional details about uploading metabolite set files or sorting results.",
