    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/pathway-level-activity-scoring/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The initial activity level (AL) score for a set of metabolites is computed using singular value decomposition (SVD) following the method described for PLAGE [7], and adapted for metabolomics data (mPLAGE)... the intensity matrix X can be used to determine an AL score for a compound in a pathway or set of metabolites in mPLAGE.",
      "asbval:note": "Core claim directly supported by passage describing SVD-based activity level computation for metabolite sets.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo11020103",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "pathway-level-activity-scoring",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Decompose a metabolite intensity matrix into quantitative pathway activity scores using singular value decomposition (SVD), enabling robust ranking of metabolic pathways without losing information through dichotomous thresholding.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:40:28.223500+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/pathway-level-activity-scoring/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The robustness of mPLAGE was evaluated on both synthetic and real data experiments and compared to both ORA and GSEA methods. The results demonstrated that the mPLAGE method is robust to noise and missing values, which is particularly important for metabolomics data... mPLAGE is generally more robust to missing features than the alternative methods tested.",
      "asbval:note": "Directly supported by benchmarking results comparing mPLAGE robustness to ORA and GSEA.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo11020103",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "pathway-level-activity-scoring",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This approach is more resilient to noise and missing peaks than over-representation analysis (ORA) or gene set enrichment analysis (GSEA).",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:40:28.223500+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/pathway-level-activity-scoring/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "we introduce Pathway Activity Level Scoring (PALS), a comprehensive and modular Python tool for metabolite set enrichment... It can be easily imported as a Python library, run as a standalone tool or used as a Web application.",
      "asbval:note": "PALS confirmed as Python library and command-line tool. Role description matches paper's description of implementing mPLAGE (PLAGE for metabolomics), ORA, and GSEA.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo11020103",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "pathway-level-activity-scoring",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "PALS (name, repo, role as command-line tool and Python library implementing PLAGE decomposition, ORA, and GSEA)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:40:28.223500+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/pathway-level-activity-scoring/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "PALS also presents a comprehensive Python-based library that can be easily run in several modes: as a standalone tool, an interactive Web application (PALS Viewer), or a Python library.",
      "asbval:note": "PALS Viewer confirmed as interactive Web application. Role as interface for running PALS and visualizing results is consistent with paper's description.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo11020103",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "pathway-level-activity-scoring",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "PALS Viewer (Web-based graphical interface for running PALS, visualizing pathway rankings)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:40:28.223500+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/pathway-level-activity-scoring/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To analyse both MFs and Mass2Motifs, Python code is provided in PALS to retrieve information on the metabolite sets as well as the peak intensity table from GNPS (Figure 7B)... For the MF analysis, Global Natural Products Social Molecular Networking (GNPS) example data were taken from the American Gut Project.",
      "asbval:note": "GNPS confirmed as source of molecular family data integrated into PALS analysis.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo11020103",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "pathway-level-activity-scoring",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "GNPS (role: provides molecular family annotations that can be grouped and analyzed alongside metabolic pathways in PALS)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:40:28.223500+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/pathway-level-activity-scoring/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The second method employs a topic-modelling approach (MS2LDA, [5]) to generate groups of peaks (called Mass2Motifs) based on the shared presence of fragment and neutral loss features in their fragmentation spectra... To analyse both MFs and Mass2Motifs, Python code is provided in PALS to retrieve information on the metabolite sets.",
      "asbval:note": "MS2LDA confirmed as source of Mass2Motif data integrated into PALS analysis.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo11020103",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "pathway-level-activity-scoring",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "MS2LDA (role: provides mass-to-motif annotations that can be grouped and analyzed alongside metabolic pathways in PALS)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:40:28.223500+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/pathway-level-activity-scoring/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "One such FCS method is pathway level analysis of gene expression (PLAGE) [7], which performs singular value decomposition (SVD)... The initial activity level (AL) score for a set of metabolites is computed using singular value decomposition (SVD) following the method described for PLAGE [7]",
      "asbval:note": "The paper cites PLAGE as reference [7] but does not provide the DOI in the passages. The DOI 10.1186/1471-2105-6-225 is the correct DOI for the original PLAGE paper (Tomfohr et al. 2005), but this specific DOI is not verbatim in the provided passages. Cannot verify from passages alone.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo11020103",
