      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "This suggests that mPLAGE is generally more robust to missing features than the alternative methods tested... mPLAGE is able to recover more original pathways in the full data using a small fraction of the features present in the original peak data, returning a higher number of true positives and fewer false positives and false negatives.",
      "asbval:note": "Robustness to missing data explicitly demonstrated.",
